# Enable git's built-in Python diff driver so hunk headers (@@ ... @@) match
# indented definitions. Without this, git's default funcname regex only matches
# column-0 definitions, so a change inside a class method shows the enclosing
# `class ...` line instead of the method. With diff=python it matches the nearest
# `def` / `async def` / `class`, i.e. the METHOD for changes inside a method.
# Especially useful for Metaflow flows, where each step is a method on the flow.
*.py diff=python
